(1135, 'Paid', 52, 89, '14', '2', 'Wood-Peckin’', 1602720000, '424', 'Season 7 Episode 2: Popeye needs a new mast, so he starts to cut down a tall tree - but a woodpecker living in that tree has other ideas. No Olive, Bluto, or spinach in this one just Popeye and a bird, sounding rather like \\\'Edward G. Robinson\\\'', 'wood-peckin', NULL, 'https://www.rediscovertelevision.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Wood-Peckin-800x450.jpg', 'HLS', 0, 'https://cdnapi.bamboo-video.com/api/entry/0_n03yfpub/flavors/playlist.m3u8?iid=628d30305b36f9556200b806', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Wood-Peckin’', 'Season 7 Episode 2: Popeye needs a new mast, so he starts to cut down a tall tree - but a woodpecker living in that tree has other ideas. No Olive, Bluto, or spinach in this one just Popeye and a bird, sounding rather like \\\'Edward G. Robinson\\\'', 'No Category', 1, 0, NULL, NULL),
(1136, 'Paid', 52, 89, '14', '1', 'Happy Birthdaze', 1602720000, '477', 'Season 7 Episode 1:Popeye\\\'s birthday, and Olive managed to get enough rationed sugar to bake him a cake, so she invites him over. Shorty is suicidal because he never gets any mail; Popeye invites him, too. But Shorty is also accident prone. He goes to wash his hands, and manages to flood Popeye right into the sewer. He assembles the ingredients, then manages to get them all over Popeye. Olive tells Popeye to wash up; Shorty runs the water, and we get another flood. Shorty decides Popeye needs to play some games, so they play baseball, golf, and hockey in Olive\\\'s living room, all ending disastrously for Popeye. Popeye manages to cut a hole in the floor; Shorty falls in, Popeye throws a rug on it, then Olive arrives carrying the cake and falls in. Soon, everyone\\\'s in the furnace in the cellar.', 'happy-birthdaze', NULL, 'https://www.rediscovertelevision.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Happy_Birthdaze-800x450.jpg', 'HLS', 0, 'https://cdnapi.bamboo-video.com/api/entry/0_71xluiu9/flavors/playlist.m3u8?iid=628d30305b36f9556200b806', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Happy Birthdaze', 'Season 7 Episode 1:Popeye\\\'s birthday, and Olive managed to get enough rationed sugar to bake him a cake, so she invites him over. Shorty is suicidal because he never gets any mail; Popeye invites him, too. But Shorty is also accident prone. He goes to wash his hands, and manages&hellip;', 'No Category', 1, 0, NULL, NULL),
(1137, 'Paid', 52, 90, '14', '20', 'The Hungry Goat', 1602720000, '409', 'Season 6 Episode 20: A goat is starving because scrap metal drives have snapped up all the cans. He finds his way onto a battleship - a giant tin can! The first sailor he sees is Popeye, who he is more than happy to turn into a goat himself.', 'the-hungry-goat', NULL, 'https://www.rediscovertelevision.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/The_Hungry_Goat-800x450.jpg', 'HLS', 0, 'https://cdnapi.bamboo-video.com/api/entry/0_8ka9ntrm/flavors/playlist.m3u8?iid=628d30305b36f9556200b806', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Hungry Goat', 'Season 6 Episode 20: A goat is starving because scrap metal drives have snapped up all the cans. He finds his way onto a battleship - a giant tin can! The first sailor he sees is Popeye, who he is more than happy to turn into a goat himself.', 'No Category', 1, 0, NULL, NULL),
(1138, 'Paid', 52, 90, '14', '19', 'Ration Fer The Duration', 1602720000, '494', 'Season 6 Episode 19: Popeye\\\'s planting a victory garden while his nephews are collecting worms for fishing. He berates them for wasting time, and tells them the story of Jack and the Beanstalk, which inspires them to plant beans. Popeye falls asleep, and dreams up a giant beanstalk. His nephews talk him into climbing to the top. Inside the giant\\\'s castle, Popee hides in the cuckoo clock and spots the giant hoarding sugar instead of gold; his hen lays tires, and his storehouses are full of other goods that were rationed in World War II. Popeye tries to walk out with a stack of tires, but the giant stops him, ultimately swatting him with a fly swatter and making him into a sandwich; the giant sprinkles Popeye with pepper, delaying the inevitable spinach briefly. Popeye defeats the giant, and gets him to sneeze all his tires into a carpet. Popeye wakes up, and the victory garden sprouts CANtaloupes (cans), POTatoes (pots), squashes (squashed tires), peaches (good tires), and finally a shoe tree right under the cast.', 'ration-fer-the-duration', NULL, 'https://www.rediscovertelevision.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Ration_Fer_The_Duration-800x450.jpg', 'HLS', 0, 'https://cdnapi.bamboo-video.com/api/entry/0_bjtfxcao/flavors/playlist.m3u8?iid=628d30305b36f9556200b806', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ration Fer The Duration', 'Season 6 Episode 19: Popeye\\\'s planting a victory garden while his nephews are collecting worms for fishing. He berates them for wasting time, and tells them the story of Jack and the Beanstalk, which inspires them to plant beans. Popeye falls asleep, and dreams up a giant beanstalk. His nephews&hellip;', 'No Category', 1, 0, NULL, NULL);
